        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Correct Ansewr in Next Question",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "4000 Synthetic learners, 4151 ASSISTments2009 learners, 19840 ASSISTments2012 learners,\n333 Statics learners ",
          "ASSISTments, Statics",
          "Answer Sequences, Questions",
          "[Sequence of Questions]",
          "BKT and DKT (the at the time state-of-the-art) have problems with the way they represent knowledge concepts:\n\n- BKT treats each knowledge concept as its own dimension and they are modelled separately,\n\n- DKT aggregates all KC into a single, not interpretable hidden vector",
          "Memory augmented Neural Networks are a foprm of enural networks with 2 modules:\n\n1. A memory matrix that sotre information\n2. A Controller module that reads and/or writes oin the matrix → changing it.\n\nMANN can be adopted for KT as it represents a theoretical improvement to LSTMs, but still has an issue with the fact that reading and writing is done on the same matrix.\n\nDKVMN addresses this by using 2 matrices: a static one that encodes information about questions and a second dynamic one that encodes knowledge on different knowledge components.",
          "Each dataset is treated separately and, in each, each question is associated with a knowledge concept apriori.\n\nInput exercise data is provided as a one-hot encoded vector.\n\nKey is updated during training but becomes fixed for the testing process.\n\nFor the value, the starting point is the difficulty of each concept. ",
          "BKT, BKT+, MANN, DKT, DKVMN",
          "Holdout Method",
          "Synthetic\n{AUC: 0.8273 - DKVMN}\n\nASSIST09\n{AUC: 0.8157 - DKVMN}\n\nSynthetic\n{AUC: 0.7268 - DKVMN}\n\nSynthetic\n{AUC: 0.8284 - DKVMN}",
          "Authors propose a new model and test it on 4 different datasets. \n\nAuthors do some hyper-parameter tuning to identify what would be the ideal combination of hyper-parameters.",
          "Does not perform cross-Validation.\n\nOnly takes into consideration answer sequences, leaving aside any representation of content or any supporting priors.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
